{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id56b705d6-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2118"},"text":"§ 2118.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Selection boards; submission of reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b705d7-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A board convened under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2106"},"text":"section 2106 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall submit its report to the Secretary. If the board has acted contrary to law or regulation, the Secretary may return the report for proceedings in revision and resubmission to the Secretary. After his final review, the Secretary shall submit the report of the board to the President for his approval, modification, or disapproval."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b705d8-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If any officer recommended for promotion is not acceptable to the President, the President may remove the name of that officer from the report of the board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b705d9-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Upon approval by the President the names of officers selected for promotion by a board convened under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2106"},"text":"section 2106 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be promptly disseminated to the service at large."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b705da-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as required by this section, the proceedings of a selection board, including a special selection board convened under section 2120, shall not be disclosed to any individual who is not a member of the board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b705db-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2118/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If the Secretary makes a recommendation under this section that the name of an officer be removed from a report of a selection board and the recommendation is accompanied by information that was not presented to that selection board, that information shall be made available to that officer. The officer shall then be afforded a reasonable opportunity to submit comments on that information to the officials making the recommendation and the officials reviewing the recommendation. If an eligible officer cannot be given access to such information because of its classification status, the officer shall, to the maximum extent practicable, be provided with an appropriate summary of the information.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id56b705dc-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/130/s1/10/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(10)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/181"},"text":"77 Stat. 181","children":[],"tail":", § 261; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/213/tII/s208/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–213, title II, § 208(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1549"},"text":"126 Stat. 1549","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 2118 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 112(b), 123(b)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4216"},"text":"132 Stat. 4216","children":[],"tail":", 4240; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dG/tLVXXXV"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. G, title LVXXXV","children":[],"tail":" [LXXXV], § 8505(a)(16), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4748"},"text":"134 Stat. 4748","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dK/tCXII/s11245/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. K, title CXII, § 11245(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4045"},"text":"136 Stat. 4045","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id56b705dd-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id56b705de-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id56b705df-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" substituted “individual who is” for “person”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s112/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 112(b)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s261"},"text":"section 261 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (a), (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s123/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 123(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 2106” for “section 251”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s123/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 123(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 2120” for “section 263”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/213"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–213","children":[],"tail":" substituted “selection board, including a special selection board convened under section 263,” for “selection board”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id56b705e0-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id56b705e1-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2012 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/213/tII/s208/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–213, title II, § 208(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1549"},"text":"126 Stat. 1549","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/112/213/tII/s208/e/1"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s263"},"text":"section 263 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and amending this section and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s262"},"text":"section 262 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall take effect on the date of enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2012","children":[],"tail":"] and the Secretary may convene a special selection board on or after that date under section 263 [now 2120] of title 14, United States Code, with respect to any error or other action for which such a board may be convened if that error or other action occurred on or after the date that is 1 year before the date of enactment of this Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id56b705e2-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id56b705e3-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Delegation of Authority","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Authority of President under subsecs. (a) and (b) of this section to approve, modify, or disapprove the report of a selection board, and to remove a name of an officer from a selection board report, respectively, delegated to Secretary of Homeland Security by Ex. Ord. No. 14106, § 1(a), (b), ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 2023","children":[],"tail":", 88 F.R. 55905, set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2101"},"text":"section 2101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
